    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <head>Biographical History</head>
      <p>Joseph Watson (1784-1841) was a lumber merchant, alderman and mayor of Philadelphia.  He later served as president of the Lehigh  Coal and Navigation Company.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
      <p>The <emph render="bold">Joseph Watson Letters</emph> consist of roughly fifty pieces of incoming and outgoing correspondence.   Writers and recipients include Henry Meyers, Jr.,  Lieutenant H. Henry, Joseph Tate (mayor of Richmond, Virginia), and others.</p>
    </scopecontent>
